(133, 1, '2022-09-06 13:32:11', '2022-09-06 13:32:11', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Matsyakara Welfare Samithi was established in the year 2004 to change the status of fishermen in the combined state of Andhra Pradesh, for their welfare and development based on 7 principles with their instructions and suggestions. It was started with fishermen in 27 district fishing villages.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>This is not only in our Andhra Pradesh but every year we organize various welfare programs in relation to other coastal states.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Saptasutras:</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list {\"ordered\":true} -->\n<ol><li><strong>Education</strong>: Establishing free tuition centers across the state in fishing villages to provide accommodation and education to college students in 167 places. Accommodation facilities providing in Nellore, Singarayakonda, student hostels, Kakinada, Vijayanagaram, Visakhapatnam, Vijayawada.</li><li><strong>Medical</strong>: Conducting medical camps in fishing villages across the state, conducting operations, providing medical aid during storms, distributing oxygen, medicines, PPI kits, Anandaiya\'s Ayurvedic medicine to everyone in the state in the most dangerous times like Corona.</li><li><strong>Sports</strong>: Organizing sports for youth development in villages. Skill development every year with sports competitions based on local village committees.</li><li><strong>Libraries</strong>: Based on the local community halls and storm shelters in the villages, we are conducting the history of the devotees of the country for orthodox tradition and personal development.</li><li><strong>Bhakti</strong>: By building temples in fishing villages, for spiritual awareness in the villages, so far 378 fishermen have been trained as priests and organized to perform pujas in our villages.<br>Tirumala Tirupati Vari Ratha Yatra and Srinivasa Kalyanam are being held. Sri Matsyanarayana Swamy Temple has been constructed on the beach of Narasapuram in West Godavari district with crores of rupees.<br>Apart from that, Tirumala Tirupati Devasthanam has given idols of Lord Venkateswara and built temples in the state.</li></ol>\n<!-- /wp:list -->', 'FISHERMEN WELFARE SOCIETY, MSS, ANDHRA PRADESH', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '8-revision-v1', '', '', '2022-09-06 13:32:11', '2022-09-06 13:32:11', '', 8, 'http://mssap.in/?p=133', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(135, 1, '2022-09-06 13:33:19', '2022-09-06 13:33:19', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Matsyakara Welfare Samithi was established in the year 2004 to change the status of fishermen in the combined state of Andhra Pradesh, for their welfare and development based on 7 principles with their instructions and suggestions. It was started with fishermen in 27 district fishing villages.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>This is not only in our Andhra Pradesh but every year we organize various welfare programs in relation to other coastal states.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Saptasutras:</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><li><strong>Education</strong>: Establishing free tuition centers across the state in fishing villages to provide accommodation and education to college students in 167 places. Accommodation facilities providing in Nellore, Singarayakonda, student hostels, Kakinada, Vijayanagaram, Visakhapatnam, Vijayawada.</li><li><strong>Medical</strong>: Conducting medical camps in fishing villages across the state, conducting operations, providing medical aid during storms, distributing oxygen, medicines, PPI kits, Anandaiya\'s Ayurvedic medicine to everyone in the state in the most dangerous times like Corona.</li><li><strong>Sports</strong>: Organizing sports for youth development in villages. Skill development every year with sports competitions based on local village committees.</li><li><strong>Libraries</strong>: Based on the local community halls and storm shelters in the villages, we are conducting the history of the devotees of the country for orthodox tradition and personal development.</li><li><strong>Bhakti</strong>: By building temples in fishing villages, for spiritual awareness in the villages, so far 378 fishermen have been trained as priests and organized to perform pujas in our villages.<br>Tirumala Tirupati Vari Ratha Yatra and Srinivasa Kalyanam are being held. Sri Matsyanarayana Swamy Temple has been constructed on the beach of Narasapuram in West Godavari district with crores of rupees.<br>Apart from that, Tirumala Tirupati Devasthanam has given idols of Lord Venkateswara and built temples in the state.</li><li><strong>Women\'s Economic Self-reliance</strong>: In fishing villages, setting up saving and fishing groups and providing financial support to women through the Department of Fisheries, setting up sewing machines and training them. Provided Rs. 25000/- to each group under the financial assistance to 736 groups through Matsyamitra groups. The fishermen women were trained on seaweed cultivation by NFDB. Training was given to women for the management of Mahila Sanghas.</li><li><strong>Self-Employment</strong> (Government Schemes): To connect the schemes given by the Government through the Department of Fisheries and various organizations to the fishermen at the field level to discuss the implementation of the schemes. In this way, we are continuously trying to protect the fishermen, coast, coastal area, ponds and rivers by providing services in 856 fishing villages in the state in economic, social, educational and medical terms. We are praying that all of you can join the organization that is providing such selfless services and come forward to provide voluntary services by taking membership from every district, mandal and village in our Andhra Pradesh to protect and develop our people.</li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->', 'FISHERMEN WELFARE SOCIETY, MSS, ANDHRA PRADESH', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '8-revision-v1', '', '', '2022-09-06 13:33:19', '2022-09-06 13:33:19', '', 8, 'http://mssap.in/?p=135', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
